fields.title: A Midsummer Night's Dream
fields.description: A Midsummer Night's Dream is a romantic comedy written by William Shakespeare in about 1595 or 1596. The play is set in Athens, and consists of several subplots that revolve around the marriage of Theseus and Hippolyta.

fields.title: The Importance of Being Earnest
fields.description: The Importance of Being Earnest is a farcical comedy by Oscar Wilde that was first performed in 1895. It is a witty and satirical play that mocks the social conventions of Victorian England, particularly the emphasis on social class and marriage.

fields.title: Hamlet
fields.description: Hamlet is a play by William Shakespeare, believed to have been written between 1599 and 1601.  The play tells the story of Prince Hamlet of Denmark, who is consumed by grief and anger after the death of his father, King Hamlet.

fields.title: Death of a Salesman
fields.description: Death of a Salesman is a tragedy by Arthur Miller. It tells the story of Willy Loman, a salesman who has lost his job and his grip on reality. He is struggling to support his family and his dreams of success are fading.

fields.title: A Streetcar Named Desire
fields.description: A tragic drama about the clash of two worlds: the fading Southern gentility of Blanche DuBois and the raw vitality of her brutish brother-in-law, Stanley Kowalski.

fields.title: The Crucible
fields.description: The Crucible is a four-act tragedy by Arthur Miller, based on the Salem witch trials of 1692. In the Puritan town of Salem, Massachusetts, a group of young girls accuses several members of the community of witchcraft, setting off a chain of events that leads to mass hysteria and injustice.

fields.title: The Phantom of the Opera
fields.description: It is based on the 1910 French novel of the same name by Gaston Leroux. The story tells of a beautiful soprano, Christine Daaé, who becomes the obsession of a mysterious, masked musical genius living in the subterranean labyrinth beneath the Paris Opéra House. The Phantom falls madly in love with Christine and tutors her in singing, helping her to become the star of the opera.

fields.title: Wicked
fields.description: The musical tells the story of Elphaba, the Wicked Witch of the West, and Glinda the Good Witch, from their days as students at Shiz University to their eventual rivalry. It explores the themes of friendship, loyalty, and courage, and challenges the traditional view of Elphaba as a villain.
